{"actual":"If the Actions-permission PUT fails (e.g. insufficient token scope), github_bootstrap() still returns successfully with a receipt claiming the bootstrap completed; the operator must know to inspect `actions_read_only_request_exit_code` in the receipt to notice the lockdown did not take effect.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"OPERATOR_FRICTION","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"github_bootstrap() invokes the Actions-permission lockdown API call, label creation, and issue creation all with check=False, so any of these failing is silently swallowed; the function only records exit codes in the final receipt rather than halting bootstrap or raising an operator-visible error.","classification":"ASSURANCE_GAP","confidence":"MEDIUM","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["Source inspection: the `_gh(root, 'api', '--method', 'PUT', f'repos/{full_name}/actions/permissions/workflow', ..., check=False)` call, the per-label `_gh(..., check=False)` calls, and the `_gh(root, 'issue', 'create', ..., check=False)` call all pass check=False, meaning util.run() will not raise NexusError on a non-zero exit; only `permission.returncode`, `result.returncode`, and `issue_result.returncode` are recorded into the receipt JSON."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/github.py:github_bootstrap"],"expected":"A security-relevant action (locking Actions workflow permissions to read-only) failing should be surfaced clearly to the operator rather than only appearing as a numeric exit code buried in a JSON receipt file.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/github.py"],"limitations":["Source-inspection only; github_bootstrap() was not executed (no authenticated GitHub CLI available, and executing it would create real external state outside this audit's scope)."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0015","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"Raise or at least emit a warning-level message when actions_read_only_request_exit_code is non-zero, rather than only recording it silently in the receipt.","record_hash":"","reproduction":["Read system/nexus_lab/github.py github_bootstrap() body."],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"LOW","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"The audit proceeded on direct task instruction without that receipt being located or verified; this observation does not itself determine which instruction source should take precedence, since status_authority for this observation is NONE.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"OPERATOR_FRICTION","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"STATUS.json declares current_mode 'R002_AUDIT_READY_LOCAL_NOT_STARTED' with open assurance_blocks including 'R002_REMOTE_PUSH_NOT_YET_RECORDED', and NEXT_ACTION.md explicitly instructs: 'Do not start the audit before the push/tag verification receipt exists.' This blind audit was nonetheless invoked and executed directly from task instructions (AUDIT_START_HERE.md / the nexus-audit skill), without any push/tag verification receipt being confirmed present, apparently bypassing the repository's own self-declared operator gate.","classification":"PROCESS_CONTRADICTION","confidence":"MEDIUM","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["STATUS.json: current_mode='R002_AUDIT_READY_LOCAL_NOT_STARTED', assurance_blocks=['R002_REMOTE_PUSH_NOT_YET_RECORDED','CLAUDE_EXTERNAL_AUDIT_NOT_YET_INGESTED'], next_action_id='ACT-R002-PUSH_TAG_VERIFY_THEN_CLAUDE_AUDIT'.","NEXT_ACTION.md: 'After the R002 overlay commit and annotated handoff tag are pushed and verified equal to origin, use the second Claude account to open AUDIT_START_HERE.md... Do not start the audit before the push/tag verification receipt exists.'","AUDIT_START_HERE.md and the nexus-audit skill both instruct the auditor to begin immediately with no check for a push/tag verification receipt."],"exact_location":["STATUS.json","NEXT_ACTION.md","AUDIT_START_HERE.md"],"expected":"If STATUS.json/NEXT_ACTION.md represent a binding precondition, the audit should not begin (or should begin only in a degraded/flagged mode) until the described push/tag verification receipt exists.","files_not_seen":["operations/receipts/ (existence/contents not inspected in this run)"],"files_seen":["STATUS.json","NEXT_ACTION.md","AUDIT_START_HERE.md",".claude/skills/nexus-audit/SKILL.md"],"limitations":["I did not search for or rule out the existence of a push/tag verification receipt outside the files listed above (e.g. under operations/receipts/); its absence is inferred from STATUS.json's own self-report ('R002_REMOTE_PUSH_NOT_YET_RECORDED') rather than an exhaustive filesystem search performed in this run.","This is a process/documentation-consistency observation, not a claim about tool correctness."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0016","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["Read STATUS.json and NEXT_ACTION.md before beginning the audit."],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"LOW","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"Have the nexus-audit skill or AUDIT_START_HERE.md check STATUS.json's assurance_blocks before proceeding, and either refuse or explicitly flag when a declared precondition is unmet.","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
